dc_description_s: Entered... April 23rd, 1832, by F.J. Huntington. Shows the states of Ohio, Indiana, Illinois, Kentucky, Missouri, and part of Michigan and West Virginia. Map no. 4 in "Atlas designed to illustrate the Malte-Brun School of Geography...". 1 map: color; 24 x 40 cm This map is in the public domain. Please attribute access and use of this digitized map to the Stephen S. Clark Library, University of Michigan Library.
